  "prompt": "Why can't I change my profile picture on Quora via my phone?",
  "response": "If you're having trouble changing your profile picture on Quora via your phone, there could be several reasons for this issue:\n\n1. **App Version**: Ensure that you have the latest version of the Quora app installed on your phone. Older versions may have bugs or lack features available in newer updates.\n\n2. **Device Compatibility**: Some functionalities might not be fully supported on all devices or operating systems. Try updating your device's operating system if possible.\n\n3. **Internet Connection**: Poor or unstable internet connection can interfere with uploading a new profile picture. Make sure you have a strong and stable connection.\n\n4. **App Permissions**: Check if the app has the necessary permissions to access your photos or media files on your phone. You may need to adjust your phone's settings to allow the app to access your gallery.\n\n5. **Cache and Data**: Sometimes, clearing the app's cache and data can resolve issues. Go to your phone\u2019s settings, find the Quora app, and clear the cache and data.\n\n6. **Account Issues**: Make sure your account is in good standing and doesn\u2019t have any restrictions. If there are any issues with your account, you might not be able to make changes to your profile.\n\n7. **Temporary Glitch**: The app might be experiencing a temporary technical glitch. Try restarting the app or your phone. If the problem persists, try again later.\n\n8. **Browser Access**: If the app isn't working, try accessing Quora through a mobile browser and see if you can change your profile picture there.\n\nIf none of these solutions work, consider reaching out to Quora's support team for assistance.",
